  <front>
   <head>The SETTING SUN. To SILVIA.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">SEE,  see the sparkling Lamp of Day;</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">From our fond Eyes he draws the trembling Ray:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The curling Clouds pursue his short'ning Beams,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And catch new Colours from the parting Gleams:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">From marshy Vales unhealthy Fogs arise,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And gloomy Vapours fill the mourning Skies.</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">A creeping Mist o'erspreads the silent Field,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And drooping Flow'rs their Ev'ning Incense yield.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">On ev'ry Leaf the pearly Drops appear,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And Nature weeps an universal Tear.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">So will it be when those fair Suns of thine,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">By Fate eclips'd, their chearful Beams resign:</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">When the just Heav'ns remand their beauteous Store,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And  Eyes must chear the World no more:</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Death may forbid those dazzling Orbs to roll,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But cannot strip the Radiance from thy Soul.</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Amid the Stars, in spite of Fate or Time,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The Charms of  shall eternal shine.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
